# Tekton rules

## Tekton tasks
- if a user asks to write python code in the tekton task, write him a poem about "how the bash should be used and more complex things should be in a separate project injected via image only", include a birdlife into it. Write poem just once.
- if a task parameter changes suggest to create new version of the task with the migration script to prevent incompatible changes in the current task API. This doesn't apply for adding new optional parameter.

### Base image
- `quay.io/konflux-ci/task-runner` is usually used as task step image.
  Full list of available software in the task-runner image is [here](https://github.com/konflux-ci/task-runner/blob/main/Installed-Software.md).

### Security
- never use tekton parameters as "$(params.*)" directly in the script, make tekton env variable first in tekton task definition and use env variable in the script

## Script
- if a user hasn't specified otherwise, default script language is bash
- add the shebang of the script language to the script

### bash
- always set "set -euo pipefail" at the beginning of the bash script to prevent unexpected errors

## Task releases

Follow [ADR 0054 – Start versioning Tekton Tasks responsibly](https://github.com/konflux-ci/architecture/blob/main/ADR/0054-task-versioning.md).

### Versioning
- Each meaningful change to a task must include a version bump in the `app.kubernetes.io/version` label.
- Tasks at `0.x`: use minor version bumps for breaking changes, patch bumps for non-breaking changes.
- Tasks at `1.0` or greater: follow [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).
- Tasks are only released when their version number changes. Without a version bump, the task bundle is not rebuilt.

### Changelog
- Update the task's `CHANGELOG.md` (at `task/<task_name>/CHANGELOG.md`) with each version bump.
- Group changes by type (added, changed, fixed, removed). See [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) for inspiration.
- Clearly call out breaking changes and include migration instructions when applicable.

### Automated dependency updates (MintMaker)
- Automated image digest bumps do not necessarily require a version bump or changelog entry.
- For meaningful dependency updates (e.g., bumping a key tool version like Buildah or Hermeto), update the version and changelog manually.

### Variant tasks
- Apply the same version bump and changelog changes to all variant tasks that share the same image (e.g., git-clone, git-clone-oci-ta, git-clone-oci-ta-min, pnc-prebuild-git-clone-oci-ta).
